        "# Import libraries\n",
        "\n",
        "%pip install arch\n",
        "\n",
        "import re\n",
        "import numpy as np\n",
        "import pandas as pd\n",
        "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
        "import yfinance as yf\n",
        "from statsmodels.tsa.arima.model import ARIMA\n",
        "from statsmodels.graphics.tsaplots import plot_acf, plot_pacf\n",
        "from arch import arch_model\n",
        "from scipy import stats\n",
        "import numpy as np\n",
        "\n",
        "np.random.seed(int(re.sub(r\"\\D\", \"\", assignment_seed)))\n",
        "\n",
        "stocks = pd.read_excel(\"https://github.com/febse/data/raw/refs/heads/main/ts/SOFIX-Stocks.xlsx\", usecols=\"A:Q\").set_index(\"Date\")\n",
        "\n",
        "dt = stocks[np.random.choice(stocks.columns)]\n",
        "\n",
        "# Split the data into training and test sets\n",
        "\n",
        "train_size = int(len(dt) * 0.85)\n",
        "train, test = dt[:train_size], dt[train_size:]\n",
        "\n",
        "# Plot the training data\n",
        "\n",
        "train.plot(title=\"Stock Price\", figsize=(12, 6))\n",
        "\n",
        "plt.xlabel(\"Date\")\n",
        "plt.ylabel(\"Price\")\n",
        "plt.title(\"Your title here\")\n",
        "plt.show()"
      ]

      "source": [
        "from statsmodels.tsa.arima.model import ARIMA\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "model_arma_30 = ARIMA(train_log_returns, order=(3, 0, 0))\n",
        "results_arma_30 = model_arma_30.fit()\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "model_arma_03 = ARIMA(train_log_returns, order=(0, 0, 3))\n",
        "results_arma_03 = model_arma_03.fit()\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "model_arma_11 = ARIMA(train_log_returns, order=(1, 0, 1))\n",
        "results_arma_11 = model_arma_11.fit()\n",
        "\n",
        "print(f\"ARMA(3,0) - AIC: {results_arma_30.aic:.2f}, BIC: {results_arma_30.bic:.2f}\")\n",
        "print(f\"ARMA(0,3) - AIC: {results_arma_03.aic:.2f}, BIC: {results_arma_03.bic:.2f}\")\n",
        "print(f\"ARMA(1,1) - AIC: {results_arma_11.aic:.2f}, BIC: {results_arma_11.bic:.2f}\")\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "all_model_results = {\n",
        "    'ARMA(3,0)': results_arma_30,\n",
        "    'ARMA(0,3)': results_arma_03,\n",
        "    'ARMA(1,1)': results_arma_11\n",
        "}\n",
        "\n",
        "aic_values = {\n",
        "    name: res.aic for name, res in all_model_results.items()\n",
        "}\n",
        "\n",
        "best_model_name = min(aic_values, key=aic_values.get)\n",
        "best_model_results = all_model_results[best_model_name]\n",
        "\n",
        "print(f\"\\nThe model with the lowest AIC is: {best_model_name}\")"
      ],

        "# Compute cumulative sum of forecasted log returns\n",
        "cum_forecasted_log_returns = forecasted_log_returns.cumsum()\n",

      "source": [
        "from sklearn.metrics import mean_squared_error\n",
        "\n",
        "# Drop NaN values from the test set and corresponding forecasts\n",
        "test_cleaned = test.dropna()\n",
        "forecast_manual_prices_cleaned = forecast_manual_prices.loc[test_cleaned.index].dropna()\n",
        "forecast_arima_prices_cleaned = forecast_arima_prices.loc[test_cleaned.index].dropna()\n",
        "\n",
        "# Ensure all series have the same length after cleaning\n",
        "common_index = test_cleaned.index.intersection(forecast_manual_prices_cleaned.index).intersection(forecast_arima_prices_cleaned.index)\n",
        "\n",
        "test_final = test_cleaned.loc[common_index]\n",
        "forecast_manual_final = forecast_manual_prices_cleaned.loc[common_index]\n",
        "forecast_arima_final = forecast_arima_prices_cleaned.loc[common_index]\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "# Compute RMSE for manual integration forecast\n",
        "rmse_manual = np.sqrt(mean_squared_error(test_final, forecast_manual_final))\n",
        "print(f'RMSE for Forecast (Manual Integration): {rmse_manual:.4f}')\n",
        "\n",
        "# Compute RMSE for direct ARIMA forecast\n",
        "rmse_arima = np.sqrt(mean_squared_error(test_final, forecast_arima_final))\n",
        "print(f'RMSE for Forecast (Direct ARIMA): {rmse_arima:.4f}')"
      ],
